<content type="str">By Staff 
Saturday, January 28, 2017 
 
Road closures and maintenance projects may affect traffic this week: 
 
City of Grand Junction Projects with Travel Restrictions 
 
■ Sewer repair and replacement project, River Road from 24 Road to Persigo Wastewater Plant: Speed limit is reduced through construction zone. Delays can be expected and alternate routes are advised. Project is anticipated to last until June. 
 
Non-City of Grand Junction Projects with Travel Restrictions 
 
■ Red Canyon Sidewalk and Pedestrian Bridge, Colorado Highway 340 east of Vista Grande Road), Mesa County Project: Construction will be weather dependent. Speed limit is reduced through construction zone. Possible traffic delays can be expected. Project anticipated to last until June. 
 
■ 2 9 1/2 Road Bridge Replacement over Grand Valley Irrigation Canal, Colorado Department of Transportation/Mesa County Project: 29 1/2 Road is closed to through traffic from Orchard Avenue to Patterson Road. 
 
Access provided for local residents. 
 
Detour route is in place. Call 640-6129 for updates. Anticipated completion date is early June.</content> 
